-{zh-cn:'''爱彼迎'''（英语：'''Airbnb'''）;zh-hk:'''Airbnb''';zh-tw:'''Airbnb''';zh-sg:'''Airbnb''';}-是一個出租住宿[[民宿|民宿]]的網站<ref>{{cite news|last=Brennan|first=Morgan|title=The Most Amazing And Absurd Places For Rent|url=http://www.forbes.com/sites/morganbrennan/2011/09/16/the-most-amazing-and-absurd-places-for-rent/|publisher=Forbes|accessdate=2012-12-13|date=2011-09-16|archive-date=2018-12-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181225005547/https://www.forbes.com/sites/morganbrennan/2011/09/16/the-most-amazing-and-absurd-places-for-rent/%20|dead-url=no}}</ref>，提供短期出租房屋或房間，讓旅行者通過網站或手機發掘和預訂世界各地的獨特房源，為近年來[[共享經濟|共享經濟]]發展的代表之一。該網站成立於2008年8月，公司總部位於美國[[加利福尼亞州|加利福尼亞州]][[舊金山|舊金山]]，是一家私有公司，由「Air-{}-bnb, Inc.」負責管理營運<ref>{{cite web|last=Grout|first=Vanessa|title=How To Use Airbnb To Profit From Your Second Home|url=http://www.forbes.com/sites/vanessagrout/2013/11/04/how-to-use-airbnb-to-profit-from-your-second-home/|publisher=Forbes|accessdate=2014-06-23|date=2013-11-13|archive-date=2018-12-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181225005546/https://www.forbes.com/sites/vanessagrout/2013/11/04/how-to-use-airbnb-to-profit-from-your-second-home/%20|dead-url=no}}</ref>。目前，Airbnb在191個國家，65,000個城市中共有400萬名房東、超過3,000,000筆房源<ref>{{Cite web|title=不怕找到爛Wi-Fi的房源！Airbnb一次推逾50項創新優化，如何迎接旅遊復甦潮？｜數位時代 BusinessNext|url=https://www.bnext.com.tw/article/66102/airbnb-winter-release|access-date=2022-03-09|work=數位時代|language=zh-TW|archive-date=2022-03-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220309042923/https://www.bnext.com.tw/article/66102/airbnb-winter-release}}</ref>。

该公司在中国品牌名为'''愛-{}-彼迎'''<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.cnbeta.com/articles/tech/595251.htm|title=Airbnb发布中国区独立品牌：愛彼迎|accessdate=2017-03-22|last=cnBeta|work=www.cnbeta.com|language=zh-CN|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170322082711/http://www.cnbeta.com/articles/tech/595251.htm|archivedate=2017-03-22|deadurl=yes}}</ref>，取「讓愛彼此相迎」之義，品牌名發布後被批評“難聽”和“性暗示”。<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/zhongwen/simp/chinese-news-39376932 |title=洋品牌取個合意的中文名有多重要？ |publisher=[[BBC|BBC]] |date=2017-03-25 |accessdate=2020-02-05 |quote=在一条介绍更名的视频下方，700多条留言大都反应名字难听，有的认为有歧义跟歌曲"爱拼才会赢"音相似，有"拉低了贵司水准"的嫌疑 |archive-date=2020-02-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200215202023/https://www.bbc.com/zhongwen/simp/chinese-news-39376932 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://36kr.com/coop/zaker/5081688.html |title=Airbnb在中國再遇冷，途家却已经将版圖擴至整個亞洲 |publisher=36氪 |date=2017-06-30 |accessdate=2020-02-05 |quote=Airbnb甚至為此将名字改成了“愛彼迎（Aibiying）”——原意為“用愛迎接彼此”，然而由于更改的中文名在漢语裏具有性暗示，一切都適得其反了 |archive-date=2020-02-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200205024742/https://36kr.com/coop/zaker/5081688.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>

用户必須註冊[[互联网|互联网]]賬號才能使用網站。每一個住宿物件都與一位[[房東|房東]]連結，房東的個人檔案包括其他用户的推薦、顧客評價、回覆評等和私信系統<ref>{{cite news|last=Yu|first=Roger|title=America's new business model: Sharing|url=http://usatoday30.usatoday.com/tech/news/story/2012-07-15/social-sharing-economy/56243142/1|publisher=USA Today|accessdate=2012-12-13|date=2011-07-06|archive-date=2012-10-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121002055758/http://usatoday30.usatoday.com/tech/news/story/2012-07-15/social-sharing-economy/56243142/1|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

== 历史 ==
===概念萌芽===
2007年，公司概念开始萌芽，两位创始人搬到三藩市居住。当时，美国工业设计社区大会正在举办，这使他们想要为开会者提供[[住宿加早餐|住宿加早餐]]<ref>{{cite web|last=Choe|first=Jeannie|title=AirBed & Breakfast for Connecting '07|url=http://www.core77.com/blog/events/airbed_breakfast_for_connecting_07_7715.asp|publisher=Core77|accessdate=28 July 2011|date=10 Oct 2007|archive-date=2015-02-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150208045711/http://www.core77.com/blog/events/airbed_breakfast_for_connecting_07_7715.asp|dead-url=no}}</ref> 。公司的初衷是想为开会者提供短期居住的房间、早餐与社交机会，解决广大开会者很难订到饱和的酒店房间的问题<ref name="Botsman, Rachel 2010">Botsman, Rachel, and Roo Rogers. "What's Mine Is Yours: the Rise of Collaborative Consumption." New York: ''Harper Business'', 2010. Print.</ref>。当时，创始人兼室友[[Chesky|Chesky]]和[[Gebbia|Gebbia]]负担不起他们在三藩市租的阁楼，所以在可容纳三个客人的客厅里放进气垫床，并且提供私房早餐<ref>{{cite web|last=Lagorio|first=Christine|title=Brian Chesky, Joe Gebbia, and Nathan Blecharczyk, Founders of AirBnB|url=http://www.inc.com/30under30/2010/profile-brian-chesky-joe-gebbia-nathan-blecharczyk-airbnb.html|publisher=Inc.com|accessdate=13 December 2012|date=19 July 2010|archive-date=2015-07-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150708043239/http://www.inc.com/30under30/2010/profile-brian-chesky-joe-gebbia-nathan-blecharczyk-airbnb.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

2008年2月，哈佛毕业生和技术架构师[[Nathan_Blecharczyk|Nathan Blecharczyk]]加入，成为AirBed & Breakfast的第三个联合创始人。<ref>{{cite web|title=Best Young Tech Entrepreneurs 2009|url=http://images.businessweek.com/ss/09/04/0421_best_young_entrepreneurs/9.htm|publisher=Bloomberg Businessweek|accessdate=13 December 2012|date=21 April 2009|archive-date=2014-12-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141221134604/http://images.businessweek.com/ss/09/04/0421_best_young_entrepreneurs/9.htm|dead-url=no}}</ref>在公司的初创阶段，创始人专注于会导致住房紧缺的高规格活动<ref>{{cite news|last=Geron|first=Tomio|title=From Crash Pad To Pizza Profitable, Start-Up Eyes Budget Travel Market|url=http://blogs.wsj.com/venturecapital/2009/06/10/from-crash-pad-to-pizza-profitable-entrepreneurs-target-budget-travel-market/|publisher=WSJ Blogs|accessdate=13 December 2012|date=10 June 2009|archive-date=2011-04-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110406235253/http://blogs.wsj.com/venturecapital/2009/06/10/from-crash-pad-to-pizza-profitable-entrepreneurs-target-budget-travel-market/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。官方网站Airbedandbreakfast.com于2008年8月11日上线<ref>{{cite web|last=Schonfeld|first=Erik|title=AirBed And Breakfast Takes Pad Crashing To A Whole New Level|url=http://techcrunch.com/2008/08/11/airbed-and-breakfast-takes-pad-crashing-to-a-whole-new-level/|publisher=TechCrunch|accessdate=13 December 2012|date=11 August 2008|archive-date=2015-08-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150804092134/http://techcrunch.com/2008/08/11/airbed-and-breakfast-takes-pad-crashing-to-a-whole-new-level/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

为了获得网站资金，创始人出产特别版早餐燕麦，名字灵感来自总统候选人[[奥巴马|奥巴马]]和[[麦凯恩|麦凯恩]]<ref>{{cite news|last=Spors|first=Kelly|title=The Business of Politics|url=http://online.wsj.com/article/SB121803424407616937.html|publisher=Wall Street Journal|accessdate=13 December 2012|date=11 August 2008|archive-date=2013-04-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130408070637/http://online.wsj.com/article/SB121803424407616937.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。两个月里，800盒燕麦以每盒40美元的价格全部售罄，为公司的发展提供了3万美元资金<ref>{{cite news|last=Peng|first=Tina|title=Where to get startup cash now|url=http://money.cnn.com/galleries/2010/smallbusiness/1003/gallery.startup_cash_now/|publisher=CNN Money|accessdate=13 December 2012|date=24 March 2010|archive-date=2015-04-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150407022954/http://money.cnn.com/galleries/2010/smallbusiness/1003/gallery.startup_cash_now/|dead-url=no}}</ref>，吸引了[[Y_Combinator_(公司)|Y Combinator]]的 [[保罗·格雷厄姆|保罗·格雷厄姆]]。<ref>{{cite web|last=Malik|first=Om|title=What Every Startup Can Learn From AirBnB|url=http://gigaom.com/2011/02/22/airbnb/|publisher=GigaOm|accessdate=13 December 2012|date=22 Feb 2011|archive-date=2015-08-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150802222406/https://gigaom.com/2011/02/22/airbnb/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

网站发布后扩张并占领了酒店和[[沙發旅行|沙發旅行]]之间的顾客。<ref>{{cite web|last=Lagorio|first=Christine|title=Brian Chesky, Joe Gebbia, and Nathan Blecharczyk, Founders of AirBnB|url=http://www.inc.com/30under30/2010/profile-brian-chesky-joe-gebbia-nathan-blecharczyk-airbnb.html|publisher=Inc.|accessdate=13 December 2012|date=19 July 2010|archive-date=2015-07-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150708043239/http://www.inc.com/30under30/2010/profile-brian-chesky-joe-gebbia-nathan-blecharczyk-airbnb.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>2009年1月， [[Y_Combinator_(公司)|Y Combinator]]邀请[[Chesky|Chesky]]，[[Gebbia|Gebbia]]和[[Blecharczyk|Blecharczyk]]加入公司进行为期三个月的训练<ref>{{cite web|last=Rao|first=Leena|title=Y Combinator's Airbed And Breakfast Casts A Wider Net For Housing Rentals As AirBnB|url=http://techcrunch.com/2009/03/04/y-combinators-airbed-and-breakfast-casts-a-wider-net-for-housing-rentals-as-airbnb/|publisher=TechCrunch|accessdate=13 December 2012|date=4 March 2009|archive-date=2015-08-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150804092106/http://techcrunch.com/2009/03/04/y-combinators-airbed-and-breakfast-casts-a-wider-net-for-housing-rentals-as-airbnb/|dead-url=no}}</ref>，他们回到三藩市时，一个可以给投资人汇报的的盈利模式已出现。

===簡化網站名稱===
2009年，网站名称从原来的Airbedandbreakfast.com 简化为A-{}-irbnb.com, 而且网站提供的产品也从气垫床和共享空间扩展为多种类型居住空间，包括整个屋子和公寓，私人房间，城堡，船，庄园，树屋，冰屋，帐篷，甚至私人岛屿等。<ref>{{cite web|title=The 26 Most Luxurious—and Unique—Vacation Spots on Airbnb Right Now|url=http://www.details.com/social/201109/best-airbnb-rentals#slide=1|publisher=Details|accessdate=13 December 2012|date=1 Sep 2012|archive-date=2015-07-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150717130548/http://www.details.com/social/201109/best-airbnb-rentals#slide=1|dead-url=no}}</ref>

2010年，15个人在[[Chesky|Chesky]]与[[Gebbia|Gebbia]]位于三藩市Rausch街的阁楼式公寓内工作。 为了给雇员提供空间，[[Brian_Chesky|Brian Chesky]]放弃他自己的卧室而居住在Airbnb的服务，直到公司搬进他们的第一个办公空间<ref>{{cite web|last=Wauters|first=Robin|title=Airbnb Founder Eats His Own Dogfood, Goes 'Homeless' For Months|url=http://techcrunch.com/2010/06/21/airbnb-brian-chesky/|publisher=TechCrunch|accessdate=13 December 2012|date=21 June 2010|archive-date=2015-08-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150804232513/http://techcrunch.com/2010/06/21/airbnb-brian-chesky/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。那一年公司继续高速增长并与2010年11月从[[格雷洛克合伙公司|格雷洛克合伙公司]]和[[红杉资本|红杉资本]]募集到[[A轮融资|A轮融资]]720万美元，并宣布过去六个月有70万订单，落实了80%订单<ref>{{cite news|last=Wortham|first=Jenna|title=Airbnb Raises Cash to Expand Budget-Travel Service|url=http://bits.blogs.nytimes.com/2010/11/10/airbnb-books-more-cash-to-connect-travelers-with-cheap-digs/|publisher=NY Times Bits Blogs|accessdate=13 December 2012|date=10 Nov 2010|archive-date=2011-08-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110822044229/http://bits.blogs.nytimes.com/2010/11/10/airbnb-books-more-cash-to-connect-travelers-with-cheap-digs/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

===風險投資進駐與國際擴張===
2011年5月25日，身为演员及[[A-Grade_Investments|A-Grade Investments]]合伙人的[[艾希顿·库奇|艾希顿·库奇]] 宣布对公司进行大笔投资，开始担任公司策略品牌顾问。<ref>{{cite news|last=Wortham|first=Jenna|title=An Actor Who Knows Start-Ups|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2011/05/26/technology/26ashton.html|publisher=''The New York Times''|accessdate=13 December 2012|date=25 May 2011|archive-date=2015-07-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150727062048/http://www.nytimes.com/2011/05/26/technology/26ashton.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>

2011年7月，Airbnb已經募得1億1980萬的[[創業投資|創業投資]]資金，來源包括[[Y_Combinator_(公司)|Y Combinator]]、{{link-en|格雷洛克合夥公司|Greylock Partners}}、[[紅杉資本|紅杉資本]]、{{link-en|安德森霍洛維茨基金|Andreessen Horowitz}}、{{link-en|DST系統|DST Systems}}、{{link-en|通用催化風險投資|General Catalyst Partners}}<ref>{{cite web|last=Malik|first=Om|title=AirBnB gets $112M in new investment|url=http://gigaom.com/2011/07/24/airbnb-gets-112-million-in-new-investment/|publisher=GigaOm|accessdate=2012-12-13|date=2011-07-24|archive-date=2012-12-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121203173835/http://gigaom.com/2011/07/24/airbnb-gets-112-million-in-new-investment/|dead-url=no}}</ref>、Youniversity Ventures合夥人[[賈維德·卡里姆|賈維德·卡里姆]]、{{link-en|凱斯·拉博伊斯|Keith Rabois}}和凱文·哈茲（Kevin Hartz）<ref>{{cite news|title=Airbnb: From Y Combinator To $112M Funding In Three Years|url=http://blogs.wsj.com/venturecapital/2011/07/25/airbnb-from-y-combinator-to-112m-funding-in-three-years/|publisher=Wall Street Journal|accessdate=2014-03-21|date=2011-07-25|archive-date=2014-03-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140323164942/http://blogs.wsj.com/venturecapital/2011/07/25/airbnb-from-y-combinator-to-112m-funding-in-three-years/|dead-url=no}}</ref>，以及A級投資公司（A Grade Investments）合夥人[[艾希頓·庫奇|艾希頓·庫奇]]和{{link-en|蓋希·奧希爾尼|Guy Oseary}}。

2011年5月，Airbnb收购德国竞争对手Accoleo。这次[[并购|并购]]开启了Airbnb在[[汉堡|汉堡]]的第一个国际办公室。<ref>{{cite web|last=Bradshaw|first=Tim|title=Airbnb moves ‘aggressively’ into Europe|url=http://www.ft.com/intl/cms/s/2/9051978c-8baf-11e0-a725-00144feab49a.html#axzz2DeVTZk9R|publisher=Financial Times|accessdate=13 December 2012|date=31 May 2011|archive-date=2016-07-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160729031206/http://www.ft.com/intl/cms/s/2/9051978c-8baf-11e0-a725-00144feab49a.html#axzz2DeVTZk9R|dead-url=no}}</ref>

2011年10月，Airbnb于[[伦敦|伦敦]]建立了第二个国际办公室。<ref>{{cite news|last=Quinn|first=James|title=Airbnb set to expand with London office|url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/finance/newsbysector/mediatechnologyandtelecoms/8801030/Airbnb-set-to-expand-with-London-office.html|publisher=''[[Telegraph_Media_Group|The Telegraph]]''|accessdate=13 December 2012|date=2 Oct 2011|archive-date=2015-09-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150925023251/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/finance/newsbysector/mediatechnologyandtelecoms/8801030/Airbnb-set-to-expand-with-London-office.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>

2012年初，Airbnb因为增长的国际顾客，新增六个国际办公室，分别位于[[巴黎|巴黎]], [[米兰|米兰]], [[巴塞罗那|巴塞罗那]], [[哥本哈根|哥本哈根]], [[莫斯科|莫斯科]]和[[圣保罗|圣保罗]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Wauters|first=Robin|title=Airbnb: 5 Million Nights Booked, Opening 6 New International Offices In Q1 2012|url=http://techcrunch.com/2012/01/26/airbnb-5-million-nights-booked-opening-6-new-international-offices-in-q1-2012/|publisher=TechCrunch|accessdate=13 December 2012|date=26 Jan 2012|archive-date=2015-09-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150920003433/http://techcrunch.com/2012/01/26/airbnb-5-million-nights-booked-opening-6-new-international-offices-in-q1-2012/|dead-url=no}}</ref> 德国分公司是这些欧洲和中亚分公司的总公司。<ref>{{cite web|last=Wauters|first=Robin|title=Airbnb Checks In With Springstar For International Expansion|url=http://techcrunch.com/2011/10/17/airbnb-checks-in-with-springstar-for-international-expansion/|publisher=TechCrunch|accessdate=13 December 2012|date=17 Oct 2011|archive-date=2015-08-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150823114055/http://techcrunch.com/2011/10/17/airbnb-checks-in-with-springstar-for-international-expansion/|dead-url=no}}</ref> 

